Sentencas: In this study, the applicability of Ba(Ce,Co,Y)O3-delta (BCCY) for a cathode of proton-conducting ceramic fuel cells was investigated.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ba(Ce,Co,Y)O3-δ Composite Cathodes for Proton-conducting Ceramic Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity and transference number of BCCY were significantly affected by a cobalt content in the oxide.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ba(Ce,Co,Y)O3-δ Composite Cathodes for Proton-conducting Ceramic Fuel Cells

Sentencas: It was found that this material showed a mixed conduction of proton, oxide ion, and electron.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ba(Ce,Co,Y)O3-δ Composite Cathodes for Proton-conducting Ceramic Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The addition of cobalt into Ba(Ce,Y)O3-delta mainly increased the electronic conductivity of materials.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ba(Ce,Co,Y)O3-δ Composite Cathodes for Proton-conducting Ceramic Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Composite electrodes with an optimum composition of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) BaCe0.7Co0.2Y0.1O3-delta (50:50 wt.%) exhibited lower polarization for the symmetrical cell test with a BaCe0.8Y0.2O3-delta electrolyte in 6.5% humidified oxygen atmosphere, as compared with La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF) itself and LSCF-BaCe0.9Y0.1O3-delta (50:50 wt.%) composite electrodes.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ba(Ce,Co,Y)O3-δ Composite Cathodes for Proton-conducting Ceramic Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The power generation test was performed at 600 degrees C-700 degrees C using a BaCe0.8Y0.2O3-delta electrolyte-supported single cell employing a LSCF BaCe0.7Co0.2Y0.1O3-delta (50:50 wt.%) composite cathode, upon feeding 3% humidified hydrogen and pure oxygen to the anode and cathode, respectively.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ba(Ce,Co,Y)O3-δ Composite Cathodes for Proton-conducting Ceramic Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The cell with a LSCF-BaCe0.7Co0.2Y0.1O3-delta (50:50 wt.%) composite cathode exhibited much higher performance than that with a LSCF electrode.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ba(Ce,Co,Y)O3-δ Composite Cathodes for Proton-conducting Ceramic Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Consequently, the introduction of cobalt into Ba(Ce,Y)O3-delta was an effective strategy for an improvement in an oxygen reduction reaction activity of a cathode material.
Titulo: La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ-Ba(Ce,Co,Y)O3-δ Composite Cathodes for Proton-conducting Ceramic Fuel Cells
